_Pa’al_ Finished Participle for Regular Shorushim:
The [[_pa’al_ finished participle]] has the following conjugation pattern for [[regular shorushim]]:
|            | *Masculine* | *Feminine* |
| *Singular* | לָבוּשׁ <br> _lauvush_ <br> [he is] dressed | לְבוּשָׁה <br> _levushau_ <br> [she is] dressed |
| *Plural*   | לְבוּשִׁים <br> _levushim_ <br> [those men are] dressed | לְבוּשׁוֹת <br> _levushos_ <br> [those women are] dressed |
The _pa’al_ participle for regular shorushim can usually be identified by the distinctive ו between the first and second root letters.
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ל, ‎ב, and ש above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
